snippet.textDisplay:
forsaken tips that you'll need to know to git gud

1: do NOT let your stamina drain to zero, it slows regeneration time.

2: use ghost burger whenever you hear 1x1x1x1 using unstable eye, its sound can be heard from anywhere on the map

3: while using noob, if low on stamina and being chased, use slateskin but do NOT use bloxy cola while slateskin is active, use ghost burger instead.

4: learn how to juke and loop, it'll allow you to survive longer.

4.5: juking is going one direction and when the killer runs in the direction your going you immideatly turn to another direction. looping is just finding a collidable object that cannot be walked over and playing ring around the rosey with the killer. sometimes the killer will switch targets or continue chasing you. be careful for killers like 1x1x1x1, john doe, noli, and coolkidd, as they all have counters to looping. killers like sixer(guest 666) and slasher dont have ranged attacks that do damage, but slashers raging pace is able to counter looping better than g666.

snippet.textDisplay:
Here is a few beginner tips from someone who is a forsaken fein

Stamina managment: i heard you talking about how you kept needing stamina, theres a way to bypass this. While in a chase, breifly check your stamina every few seconds, and stop running when you reach about 5-10 stamina, this way, you regain stamina way quicker

Abilites: you didnt use your abilites that were helpful during rounds, you can use them by checking the buttons on the bottom right of your screen during game, if you want to see what a ability does, click on a survivor in your inventory, and click the book looking thing, which will give a runthrough of what each ability does for that character.

Character groups: there is 3 different survivor groups, sentinals, survivalists, and supports. Noob (the character you were using) is a survivalist. Survivalists are lone survivors and use what they have to protect themselves, but sometimes can be dependant on the team. Support characters are characters that help the team and prioritize doing so. They can heal, stall chases, ect. And sentinals are the survivors who can fight back. A sentinals goal is to help the team by stunning (for example, guests punch) the killer, tanking hits for others (guest works well for this as well), ect. So if you like helping yourself, i recommend using noob, veeronica, 007n7. If you like helping by healing, consider elliot, builderman, taph, dusekkar. If you wanna put a real KICK in the killers face by fighting back, maybe try out guest 1337, shedletsky, chance, or two time!

Help: this goes without saying, but help the team. Its in the rules (course, you already knew that)

Hope this helps!

snippet.textDisplay:
Here's some tips that might be useful:

Side note: If the killer is near you, their soundtrack plays and survivors and killers both have unique skins that have a different appearance and the killer skins have different chase themes, intros and custom voicelines, etc.
(I suggest not buying survivor nor killers unless your tryna look cool ig)

Survivor Tips:
1. When the killer is chasing you, try juking and predicting their attacks (it will be easier once you know all the killers) and save stamina too when being chased 
2. It's recommended to just look at the killer when also being chased
3. Save money for better survivors and killers

Here are the survivors and their movesets:

Noob:
Ghostburger - Makes you partially Invisible for a short time
Bloxy Cola - Gives you speed 2 (recommended for lms (last man standing))
Slateskin - Gives you a slate looking skin that gives you armor but makes you slow

And the rest, just research for them or look in the game

Killers:
Slasher moveset:
Slash - deals 10 damage to survivors (I think)
Gashing wound - damages survivors to more than half health
Raging pace - You get slow but when you slash, you do a dash

It's recommended to use abilities to kill survivors faster (I do not advice relying on abilities too much, so save your abilities waisely)

Killer Tips:

1. Know what survivors your gonna have to deal with and what abilities they have
2. Predict where they will be
3. Save stamina just like survivors

Random Tips:
Adjust your settings:
Put show Hitboxes on for killers like c00lkid and 1x1x1x1 cuz they'll do a range type of attacks and put epilepsy mode on so you'll see better when 1x uses one of his abilities where your screen glitches
Also:
Noli will have clones as sort of a 'hallucination' when doing a "fake generator" that acts like the killer but misses their attacks every time, so look away from a clone to make them disappear, also, when the generators will randomly turn purple, it means Noli is using his teleport ability to teleport to a random generator when a survivor is near said generator

These are all the beginner tips I have for you for now, I advise calling a professional forsaken player to teach you next time

Hey Brandon! Biggest fan when you started playing baldi's basics... Here's some tips!

1. Never let your stamina hit 0% it takes a long time to regenerate... So keep an eye on that stamina bar!

2. Some characters have special abilities! Supporter, sentinel, and survivalist!

3 when your playing the survivors that turn invisible for a few seconds (007n7, Noob, Two time, ect) try using the abilities when your last man standing! It makes the killer harder to find you,

4. The red walls can only be access for killers! Use that as an advantage

5. Never let survivalist last when your killer, just like number 3, it would be harder to find them.

6. Noli has hallucination abilities, which can trick you at times, one of them will be the generator hallucination, pay attention to the sound it makes, if it sounds glitchy, it's fake, if the "$" sign is different it's fake! 7. When playing as slasher and your about to lose stamina, use raging pace, it regenorates your stamina, and deals more damage, especialy when using gushing wound!

Don't pressure yourself when making videos Brandon, thanks for the childhood you created for me, it was fun and funny watching you vids, take care with your family.
